.TH "drm_crtc_add_crc_entry" 9 "drm_crtc_add_crc_entry" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_crtc_add_crc_entry \- Add entry with CRC information for a frame
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_crtc_add_crc_entry
.BI "(struct drm_crtc *crtc "  ","
.BI "bool has_frame "  ","
.BI "uint32_t frame "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *crcs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "crtc" 12
CRTC to which the frame belongs
.IP "has_frame" 12
whether this entry has a frame number to go with
.IP "frame" 12
number of the frame these CRCs are about
.IP "crcs" 12
array of CRC values, with length matching #drm_crtc_crc.values_cnt
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For each frame, the driver polls the source of CRCs for new data and calls
this function to add them to the buffer from where userspace reads.
